# AI Work Progress - Sweet.TV Kodi Addon

## Project Goal
Build a Kodi addon for sweet.tv that provides native TV experience (live channels, EPG, archive, VOD) using IPTV Manager integration.

## Phases

### Phase 1: Core Live TV + EPG [IN PROGRESS]
- [x] Analyze Enigma2 reference plugin for API understanding
- [x] Plan architecture and discuss with user
- [ ] Set up repo structure (README, configs, addon skeleton)
- [ ] Implement sweet.tv API client (auth, channels, EPG, streams)
- [ ] Implement IPTV Manager integration
- [ ] Build addon entry point and URL router
- [ ] Create settings UI
- [ ] Implement device pairing flow
- [ ] Implement live stream playback with lifecycle management
- [ ] Test and validate

### Phase 2: Archive/Catchup [PLANNED]
- [ ] Browse channels with archive support
- [ ] Browse archive by day
- [ ] Play archived programs

### Phase 3: Parental Lock [PLANNED]
- [ ] Adult channel filtering
- [ ] PIN protection for adult content
- [ ] Integration with Kodi parental controls

### Phase 4: Subscription Info [PLANNED]
- [ ] Fetch and display subscription details
- [ ] Show plan type and expiry

### Phase 5: Additional Features [PLANNED]
- [ ] VOD/Movies (genres, collections, trailers)
- [ ] Search (movies + EPG records)
- [ ] Device management
- [ ] Quality selection
- [ ] Slovak localization
- [ ] Favorites/recently watched

## Technical Decisions
- IPTV Manager for native TV section (user choice)
- Kodi 21+ only, no legacy support
- English first, localization later
- Device pairing auth (not username/password - API requirement)

## Reference
- Enigma2 plugin: tmp/archivczsk-doplnky/plugin_video_sweettv/
- sweet.tv API: https://api.sweet.tv/ (all POST, JSON)
